  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_radiofrequency_ablation">Radiofrequency Ablation</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_clinical_intervention">CLINICAL INTERVENTION</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_radiofrequency_ablation">Radiofrequency Ablation</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_radiofrequency_ablation">RFA</xref>) is a procedure that uses radio waves to heat and destroy abnormal 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_cell">CELLS</xref>. The radio waves travel through electrodes (small devices that carry electricity). 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_radiofrequency_ablation">Radiofrequency Ablation</xref>
 may be used to treat cancer and other conditions.        </p>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_radiofrequency_ablation">Radiofrequency Ablation</xref>, see the 
              <xref href="https://www.cancer.gov/dictionary?CdrID=44865"
               scope="external"
               format="html">National Cancer Institute website</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
